Dickens Wasonga @PeopleDailyKe The government will create 6.5 million jobs during the implementation of the five-year National Medium Term Development Plan whose dissemination in the 47 counties began on Monday in Kisumu. According to Finance Cabinet secretary Henry Rotich, the plan, whose theme is “Transforming lives, by advancing socio-economic development through the Big Four,” also seeks to achieve a seven per cent economic growth in the next four years. Savings and investment During the plan’s implementation period which covers 2018-2022, the CS said that the government hopes to see an increase in savings and investments, as a percentage of the Gross Domestic Product (GDP), which is projected to grow from 18.8 per cent to 23.2 per cent and 24.4 per cent to 27.2 per cent, respectively. In a speech read on his behalf by the ICT Principal Secretary Jerome Ochieng in Kisumu, the CS said the plan seeks to not only increase  the level of savings and investment in the country , but also enhance  the productivity of investment in all sectors of the economy.